\begin_inset Formula $x^{2}=4a$
\end_inset

 we get 
\begin_inset Formula $4a\left(x^{2}-1\right)=4c$
\end_inset

 which is true.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Case
Suppose directly that 
\begin_inset Formula $x^{2}\equiv1\:\mod\:4$
\end_inset

.
 This indicates that 
\begin_inset Formula $4\mid x^{2}-1$
\end_inset

, in other words 
\begin_inset Formula $x^{2}-1=4a$
\end_inset

 for some 
\begin_inset Formula $a\in\mathbb{Z}$
\end_inset

.
 We showed earlier that the statement 
\begin_inset Formula $4\mid\left(x^{4}-x^{2}\right)$
\end_inset

 can be written as 
\begin_inset Formula $4\mid x^{2}\left(x^{2}-1\right)$
\end_inset

 and is equivalent to saying 
\begin_inset Formula $x^{2}\left(x^{2}-1\right)=4c$
\end_inset

 for some 
\begin_inset Formula $c\in\mathbb{Z}$
\end_inset

.
